This project is inspired by design patterns from:

  - OpenSpec (https://github.com/jbellis/openspec)
  - spec-kit (GitHub's specification-driven development tooling)

The pipeline concepts (stages, gates, state machine) and contract-first
approach draw intellectual lineage from these predecessors while
introducing:

  - Machine-verifiable gates (compile + lint + blacklist)
  - .state.md as single source of truth for pipeline state
  - CORRECTIONS mechanism for auditable mid-implementation pivots
  - IDE-agnostic integration via MCP + adapters

Internal lineage note:
  pl-pipeline's contract-centric thinking (artifact identity, event
  journal, drift detection) was influenced by an internal protocol
  specification called "piao-pipeline" which is not released as part
  of this distribution. The consumer of pl-pipeline does not need to
  know about or depend on piao-pipeline.
